-- Kuwait's Zain Repays $4 Billion Loans After Africa Asset Sale, Qabas Says
-- Fiona MacDonald
-- 2010-06-20T06:26:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-20/kuwait-s-zain-repays-4-billion-loans-after-africa-asset-sale-qabas-says.html

          
          
             Mobile Telecommunications Co., the
Kuwaiti phone company known as Zain, repaid about $4 billion in
loans to 50 local and international lenders,  Al-Qabas  reported,
without saying where it got the information.  
 Zain used proceeds from the sale of its African assets to
Bharti Airtel Ltd. to repay the loans, the newspaper said.  
